# Mothership hooks → JSVM boundary

Source: `packages/pockethost/src/mothership-app/src/lib/handlers/` and `src/hooks/`.
Output: `pb_hooks/mothership.js` via `pnpm --filter pockethost-mothership-app build` (tsdown).

Hooks run in **PocketBase Goja JSVM**, not Node. tsdown targets Node for bundling only.

## Imports

| OK | Not OK |
|----|--------|
| `$common/*` → `packages/pockethost/src/common/*` (must be JSVM-safe; tsconfig path required) | `$common` barrel for runtime imports (pulls unrelated Node code) |
| `$util/*` under `mothership-app/src/lib/util/` | CLI services, dashboard, npm packages with Node/browser APIs |
| Relative imports within `mothership-app/` | Type-only `$common` imports are fine (erased at compile) |
| PocketBase globals (`$app`, `$security`, …) | Node `crypto`, `fs`, `async`/`await` in bundled code |

**Rule:** Shared logic used by hooks and CLI/dashboard lives in `common/`. Code imported into hooks must be **Goja-safe** (sync, no Node/browser APIs). Prefer `$common/<file>` subpath imports over the `$common` barrel.

Add new subpaths to `mothership-app/tsconfig.json` `"$common/*"` (already mapped to `../common/*`).

## JSVM-safe common code

When `common/` modules are bundled into `pb_hooks`:

- Synchronous only
- No `async`/`await`, Promises, timers
- No Node or browser-only APIs (`atob`, `fetch`, `crypto` module)
- No deps that pull in BigInt-heavy crypto (e.g. `@noble/*`) unless verified in Goja
- Prefer manual byte/base64 parsing over platform helpers

Read `.cursor/skills/pocketbase-jsvm/constraints.md` before adding hook-facing common helpers.

## Custom route JSON bodies

Use `e.bindBody()` + `DynamicModel`, then `JSON.parse(JSON.stringify(data))` before validators — not `JSON.parse(readerToString(e.request.body))` except webhooks. Wrap `$common` validation `Error` throws as `BadRequestError`. See `.cursor/skills/pocketbase-jsvm/request-body.md` and [quirks.md](quirks.md).

## `$app.store()` — JSON boundaries

Never store or mutate plain JS objects in `$app.store()` across concurrent requests (Goja VM pool — racy panic under load). Use `JSON.stringify`/`JSON.parse` at read/write boundaries; incremental updates via `setFunc`. Mothership helper: `$util/appStoreJson` (`getAppStoreJson`, `setAppStoreJson`, `updateAppStoreJson`). Details: `.cursor/skills/pocketbase-jsvm/app-store.md`.

## Live process watches hooks

PocketBase watches hook JS on disk and **reloads the JSVM when files change without exiting the process**. Stop mothership before any operation that swaps hook files on a live tree (`git checkout`, partial deploy). Reload only after the full bundle is consistent on disk (see `v39.sh --forward`).

## After every hook change

1. `pnpm --filter pockethost-mothership-app build`
2. **Zero** `[UNRESOLVED_IMPORT]` warnings in build output
3. `pnpm check:mothership-hooks` before commit (CI enforces fresh `pb_hooks/`)

If build warns `Module not found, treating it as an external dependency`, the hook will **fail silently at runtime** in JSVM. Fix tsconfig paths or import path before shipping.

## Do not edit by hand

`pb_hooks/mothership.js` and `mothership.pb.js` are generated. Edit TypeScript under `src/lib/handlers/` only.
